From: vyos-ls1046a-build M3-3 step 6 <noreply@vyos-ls1046a-build>
Date: 2026-05-27
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: chunk bman_release() in 8-buffer batches (fix BMan ErrInt)

M3-3 step 6 blocker A (spec sec 6.1.5, "BMan Invalid Command Verb").

Root cause: BMan RCR (Release Command Ring) verb byte encodes the buffer
count in a 4-bit BUFCOUNT field (bman.c:116 BUFCOUNT_MASK = 0x0f) and
bman_release() asserts num in [1,8] (bman.c:746). Any value > 8 produces
a malformed RCR command verb that the QBMan portal rejects with
"ErrInt: Invalid Command Verb", and the release is silently dropped --
no buffers reach the pool, RX stalls.

Both AF_XDP refill call sites (attach-time seed loop and napi-hooked
refill from 0084) were passing up to 32 buffers to bman_release() in
one shot, hitting the BUFCOUNT overflow on every batch.

Mainline dpaa_eth.c:1624 (dpaa_eth_refill_bpool) respects this contract
by using a fixed 8-buffer chunk -- mirror that pattern at both sites.

DPAA_ASSERT() is a no-op without CONFIG_FSL_DPAA_CHECKING=y so this
corruption was silent in our vpp-flavor build; it only surfaced via
QBMan err-IRQ counters under sustained ingress.

Spec ref: M3-3 step 6 blocker A.
Predecessors: 0084 (NAPI-hooked BMan refill), 0085 (TX ZC + backpressure).

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
index 9337cb8..aa71116 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/af_xdp_pool_main.c
@@ -239,7 +239,17 @@ return -ENODEV;
 			dma_addr_t dma = xsk_buff_xdp_get_dma(handles[i]);
 			bm_buffer_set64(&bmbs[i], dma);
 		}
-		bman_release(bpool, bmbs, (u8)n);
+		/* BMan RCR verb byte BUFCOUNT_MASK = 0x0f, HW-valid range 1..8
+		 * only (bman.c:746 DPAA_ASSERT). Mirror the mainline dpaa_eth.c
+		 * refill contract (8 at a time). Spec M3-3 step 6, patch 0086.
+		 */
+		{
+			u32 chunk_off;
+			for (chunk_off = 0; chunk_off < n; chunk_off += 8) {
+				u8 chunk = (u8)min_t(u32, 8u, n - chunk_off);
+				bman_release(bpool, &bmbs[chunk_off], chunk);
+			}
+		}
 		seeded += n;
 	}
 	if (seeded < DPAA1_XSK_INITIAL_SEED / 2)
@@ -644,7 +654,18 @@ n = xsk_buff_alloc_batch(pool, handles, ARRAY_SIZE(handles));
 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
 bm_buffer_set64(&bmbs[i], xsk_buff_xdp_get_dma(handles[i]));
 if (n) {
-bman_release(bpool, bmbs, (u8)n);
+/* Chunk bman_release() in 8-buffer batches; HW BUFCOUNT field is
+ * 4 bits and rejects num > 8 as Invalid Command Verb. XSK-side
+ * counter still bumps once per non-empty alloc batch. Mirror of
+ * attach-time seed loop. Spec M3-3 step 6, patch 0086.
+ */
+{
+u32 chunk_off;
+for (chunk_off = 0; chunk_off < n; chunk_off += 8) {
+u8 chunk = (u8)min_t(u32, 8u, n - chunk_off);
+bman_release(bpool, &bmbs[chunk_off], chunk);
+}
+}
 priv->xsk_bman_refill_batches++;
 }
 }
